				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, after 2 years of crash-exploits, and mailing them about it several people here, I had someone call FC offices to come to IRC, and then I had to argue with Korre for over an hour before he accepted to get a demonstration ingame to crash him so he could see the severity of the problem, and then I handed them the packets. (He, and Ørjan, and Sillirion, actually first refused to get it shown, thats how much Funcom cares about the security for their players and the community. They would rather have the servers exploitable, than to accept information from a player they know are angry at them, and yet they contacted me first again this time, apparently just to argue and BS with me.) 
<br />

<br />
15.8.2 came out today, where the crashpackets have been fixed (most of them). 
<br />

<br />
So, after several people mailing them about it for 2 years, nothing happends, but the split second someone show's it to them directly ingame and they realize just how bad the exploit is, then they fix it within 24 hours. 
<br />

<br />
And the way Funcom thank someone for showing it to them and giving them the exact information and how to use it? The account I used to show Korre the exploit on, is banned. 
<br />

<br />
Sillirion: "we dont actively search for banned players on accounts, but when they bring their presence to our attention, we ban the account they use". 
<br />

<br />
I just can't get over the lowscum and unethical backstabbing nature of FC's employees, and dispite that it will hurt the IGN users, I won't put myself in a position anymore where I just benefit the lowscum liars I hate by helping them for their own good. 
<br />

<br />
You can say "drama" all you want, but I was never the one wanting drama, FC wants it that way, instead of prioritizing security and issues they prioritize personal issues instead, acting like childs. 
<br />

<br />
I'm done doing anything else with IGN, I'm done risking someone's account just so I can go ingame and fix things when Funcom screws up for all the bots. I didn't expect any "thanks" from Funcom, but I sure as hell didn't expect then to fuck me from behind right after helping them either. Infact, the only thing I asked was that they never contact me again. Which they have several times, here on HQ, after I'm no longer a FC customer, long after i've mailed them that I do not want them to contact me again by mail or any other method, yes they've done so numerous times outside of FC's jurestiction every time they they need to "fish" for info or help if they hear I have information about bugs etc. I'm pretty sure I'm far from the only one they contact to fish for info. 
<br />
If thei're so eeger for information, why don't they simply read their mails when people report the bugs by mail then? Weird/sicko if you ask me. 
<br />

<br />
I also told Sillirion personally what i thought of that type of lowscum behavior, in which he banned me from the IRC server aswell 
<br />

<br />
"Closing Link: Amona by irc.funcom.com (G-lined (Req Silirrion))" 
<br />

<br />
I guess the guy can't take heat in PM's either, and see the need to abuse some power. He even went as far as insinuating i've "blackmailed" them to 
<br />
deliver information on certain demands, which is BS and lies, I've never asked for anything, i've only stated: 
<br />
"It's been 2 years now, and you wont listen about this exploit, now, either you finally listen, and come and see the exploit in action for yourselfs, and then I deliver the information to you PERSONALLY so I KNOW FOR SURE that you actually READ the information this time, or I see no other choice than to publish the information so you're forced to actually fix it in a hurry. It's been 2 years of no replies on that erro now, it's time you listen. I don't trust anymore that you even read mails, cause you don't reply on them, and the error hasnt been fixed, thus the ONLY thing i trust now is if i witness someone from FC actually SEEING it for themselves, cause you've prooven yourself over and over again NOT to be trustworthy." 
<br />

<br />
I didnt ask to get unbanned or anything like that, not even close. Oh, and then I repeated what i've always said "STOP CONTACTING me when you want to fish for information like this from now on, I'm no longer a FC customer, you have no business in contacting me, for god's sake, put up a poster in your office or something telling FC employees NOT to contact me, cause every time they contact me, they just leave in middle of conversations all the time without notice, it's rude to do that where I live.
<br />
Either that, or they give me some bullshit promises they break every single time and then deny in public later." 
<br />

<br />
Well, Korre saw the exploit at first hand when he finally accepted to get it shown to him, and then, and ONLY then did they finally listen. 
<br />

<br />
To be done with immature, stubborn loosers, I need to be done with Funcom, that unfortunately involves also being done with IGN aswell. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
I won't shut down the IGN network, but I would be glad if people respect this, and stop using IGN by themselves, cause every bot out there, IGN or any other bot-type, actually benefits Funcom, cause it makes the game atleast 1% more interesting for many players, and that 1% extra is often the difference needed for some to stay or leave AO. That way Funcom gets more money, and can keep on treating players, and people who help them like shit, I wont be part of that sick twisted game any more. 
<br />

<br />
I've never met less ethical people, making more digusting decisions than the people at Funcom, hurting the community and the players in ways most people don't even know about. I feel sorry for anyone addicted to AO, cause Funcom is the drugdealer you depend on giving you your "fix". 
